:::summary
Geometry — from the Greek *ge* (earth) and *metrein* (to measure) — is the mathematical study of shape, size, relative position, and the properties of space. From Euclid's *Elements* to the curved spacetime of Einstein's general relativity, geometry has been both a model of rigorous reasoning and one of humanity's deepest tools for understanding the physical world.
